command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateDefectType
command.description: This command creates a Defect Type, as well as any subsequent relationships (parent-to-child and child-to-parent).

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UpdateDefectType
command.description: This command updates a specific Defect Type, as well as its related relationships.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteDefectTypeList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Defect Types, as well as their related relationships.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateDefectGroup
command.description: This command creates a Defect Group, as well as any subsequent relationships (parent-to-child and child-to-parent).

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UpdateDefectGroup
command.description: This command updates a specific Defect Group.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteDefectGroupList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Defect Groups.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.AssignNonConformanceTransitionMailAddressList
command.description: This command creates an XML file with the list of e-mail addresses associated to Opcenter EX DS Roles. These e-mail addresses receive notifications when the specified Non-Conformance Transition (related to a specific Non-Conformance Lifecycle) occurs.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.AssignNonConformanceTransitionRoleList
command.description: This command creates an XML file with the list of Opcenter EX DS Roles allowed to perform actions on a specific Non-Conformance Transition (related to a specific Non-Conformance Lifecycle).

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateNonConformanceTransition
command.description: This command creates a new Transition for a specific Quality Non-Conformance Lifecycle.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteNonConformanceTransitionList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Non-Conformance Transitions.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.RemoveNonConformanceTransitionMailAddressList
command.description: This command removes the e-mail addresses of the Opcenter EX DS Roles assigned to a specific Non-Conformance Transition (of a specific Non-Conformance Lifecycle).

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.RemoveNonConformanceTransitionRoleList
command.description: This command removes specific Opcenter EX DS Roles from the list of those previously assigned to receive notifications related to a Non-Conformance Transition (of a specific Non-Conformance Lifecycle).

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.GetNonConformanceTransitionRoleMailList
command.description: This command returns the list of Authorized Roles and E-Mail Addresses configured to receive notifications for a specific Transition of a Non-Conformance.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateNonConformanceStatus
command.description: This command creates a Non-Conformance Status.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UpdateNonConformanceStatus
command.description: This command updates a specific Non-Conformance Status.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteNonConformanceStatusList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Non-Conformance States.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateSkill
command.description: This command creates a Skill. A Skill represents a specific requirement that can either be directly associated to Process Operations and Work Order Operations or assigned to specific Users through Certifications.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateReworkCodeList
command.description: This command creates a list of Rework Codes. A Rework Code represents an association involving a Process, which has been defined to rework an item, a Defect (or a group of Defects) and a Final Material.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteReworkCodeList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Rework Codes.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UpdateNonConformanceLifecycle
command.description: This command updates a specific Non-Conformance Lifecycle.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UADMCreateMaterialDefinition
command.description: This command creates a Material. The prefix “UADM” indicates that the command is invoked by the default AppU4DM UI. This command can be extended in any case, and the developed custom logic can be called from the UI instead.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UADMUpdateMaterialDefinition
command.description: This command updates the specified Material. The prefix “UADM” indicates that the command is invoked by the default AppU4DM UI. This command can be extended in any case, and the developed custom logic can be called from the UI instead.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.EnableLocationMachineForCompleteByDifferentUser
command.description: This command enables a Machine to permit a Work Order Operation to be completed by a user other than who started its execution.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteNonConformanceLifecycleList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Non-Conformance Lifecycles.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateToolDefinition
command.description: This command creates a Tool Definition.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UADMCreateToolDefinition
command.description: This command creates a Tool Definition. The prefix “UADM” indicates that the command is invoked by the default AppU4DM UI. This command can be extended in any case, and the developed custom logic can be called from the UI instead.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UADMCreateNewToolDefinitionRevision
command.description: This command creates a new Revision of the specified Tool Definition. The prefix “UADM” indicates that the command is invoked by the default AppU4DM UI. This command can be extended in any case, and the developed custom logic can be called from the UI instead.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UpdateToolDefinition
command.description: This command updates a specific Tool Definition.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteToolDefinitions
command.description: This command deletes one or more Tool Definitions, provided that the specified versions are not in use.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateNonConformanceLifecycle
command.description: This command creates a Quality Non-Conformance Lifecycle.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateWorkOperationType
command.description: This command creates the type of an Operation or a Work Order Operation. The type determines how the Operation / Work Order Operation will behave at runtime.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateNewMaterialDefinitionRevision
command.description: This command creates a new Revision (version) of the specified Material.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateDefectGroupContextualization
command.description: This command creates an association involving a Defect Group, a Material and a Machine.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.RemoveDefectGroupContextualization
command.description: This command removes the association involving a specific Defect Group, specific Materials and specific Machines.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateDefectTypeContextualization
command.description: This command creates an association involving a Defect Type, a Material and a Machine.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.RemoveDefectTypeContextualization
command.description: This command removes the association involving a specific Defect Type, specific Materials and specific Machines.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteWorkOperationTypeList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Work Operation Types, provided that the specified entities are not in use.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.SetNonConformanceStatusIsScrapped
command.description: Sets attribute IsScrap on the specified Non-Conformance Status for a specific Non-Conformance Lifecycle.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.SetNonConformanceStatusIsFrozen
command.description: Sets attribute IsLock on the specified Non-Conformance Status for a specific Non-Conformance Lifecycle.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.LinkSubstrateDefinitionToMachine
command.description: Links one or more specified Machines (or Equipment Types) to a specific Substrate Definition.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UnlinkSubstrateDefinitionToMachine
command.description: Removes the specified list of links between a Substrate Definition and Machines (or Equipment Types).

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateNonProductiveActivity
command.description: This command creates a Non-Productive Activity.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UpdateNonProductiveActivity
command.description: This command updates a specific Non-Productive Activity.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteNonProductiveActivityList
command.description: This command deletes one or more Non-Productive Activities.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.CreateTeam
command.description: This command creates a Team.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.DeleteTeam
command.description: This command deletes a specific Team.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UpdateTeam
command.description: This command updates the details about the specific Team.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.LinkSkillsToTeam
command.description: This command links one or more specified Skills to a specific Team.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UnLinkSkillsFromTeam
command.description: This command removes the specified links related to the Skills required to join a Team.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.LinkUsersToTeam
command.description: This command links one or more Users to a specific Team.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.UnLinkUsersFromTeam
command.description: Removes the specified list of links between a Team and Users.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Commands.TCM2CreateToolDefinitionList
command.description: Creates a list of Tool Definitions imported from an external system. Used in case of integration with Teamcenter Manufacturing.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Events.OnPLMCreateToolDefinitionList
event.description: Event triggered whenever a list of Tool Definitions is created.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Events.OnJoinTeam
event.description: This event is fired when a User joins the Team.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.MatTool.MSModel.Events.OnLeaveTeam
event.description: This event is fired when a User leaves the Team.
